==English==
===Etymology===
French, “stroke of state”.
===Noun phrase===
'''coup d’état''' (''plural'' '''coups d’état''')

#The sudden overthrow of a government, differing from a revolution by being carried out a small group of people who replace only the leading figures.
{{seeCites}}

